====== DADI Meeting on Gravitational Waves ======

Two-day informal meeting where VO developers can understand the issues and needs of GW people and where GW people can learn about the VO and get technical support for on-going or future development of VO tools.

(Top level DADI page: [[open:wp4:start|WP4: Data Access, Discovery and Interoperability (DADI)]])

==== Dates ====

31 May-1 June 2016

==== Location ====

Observatoire de Strasbourg, 11 rue de l'Université, Strasbourg, France

==== Main Topics ====

   * VOevent/alert and GW
   * Tools to help defining follow-up strategy:
      * Skymap visualization and tiling
      * Galaxy catalogs and usage for prioritization
   * Tutorial on the scientifc usage of the VO


   

==== Tutorial ====

**//Please install Aladin and TOPCAT on your computer//** {{:open:wp4:install_instructions.pdf|Install Instructions}}

[[https://www.astron.nl/asterics/lib/exe/fetch.php?media=open:wp4:highenergytutorial_astericsmadrid_dec10.pdf|Multi-instrument, multi-wavelength study of high energy sources with the virtual Observatory]]

==== Programme ====

The meeting will begin at 9:00 on 31 May 2016 and likely finish in the afternoon on 1 June 2016. The initial programme was purely indicative and evolved as the meeting progressed. The programme shown below is the final one.


**May 31st** //Salle de Cours//


9:00 Welcome

   * Introduction -- A few words about ASTERICS ad DADI (Data Access Discovery and Interoperability) (Francoise){{:open:wp4:wp4_gw2016.pdf|pdf}}
   * Introduction -- Scope of the meeting (Eric)
   * Quick recap of the science context : GW observations so far (Eric) {{:open:wp4:presentation_intro.pdf|pdf}}



10:30 -- 11:00 Coffee break

   * VO in a nutshell from [[http://ivoa.net]]
   * Discussion on VOevent std and its application to GW observations - [[http://www.ivoa.net/documents/VOEvent/20110711/|Current VOEvent standard]] - [[http://www.ivoa.net/documents/VOEventTransport/20160503/index.html|Current VOEvent Transport Protocol]] 
   * VO tools for astronomers and handling GW skymaps
   * Working with probability sky maps: tools for astronomers and suggestions (Giuseppe) {{open:wp4:giuseppe_gw2016.pdf|pdf}}
   * Useful information on HiPS (Hierarchical Progressive Survey) and MOC (HEALPix Multi-Order Coverage map): {{http://www.ivoa.net/documents/MOC/20140602/index.html|MOC IVOA Standard}} {{http://www.aanda.org/articles/aa/abs/2015/06/aa26075-15/aa26075-15.html|Hierarchical Progressive Surveys : Fernique et al, 2015 A&A 578 A114}}
   * Obscore standard (main information about observations) {{http://www.ivoa.net/documents/ObsCore/20111028/index.html|current version V1.0}} {{http://www.ivoa.net/documents/ObsCore/20160330/index.html|Proposed V1.1}}

12:30 -- 14:00 Lunch break

   * Tutorial  [[https://www.astron.nl/asterics/lib/exe/fetch.php?media=open:wp4:highenergytutorial_astericsmadrid_dec10.pdf|Multi-instrument, multi-wavelength study of high energy sources with the virtual Observatory]] 
  
  Other tutorials can be found [[http://www.euro-vo.org/?q=science/scientific-tutorials|here]], in particular one about advanced functionalities in TOPCAT [[https://www.astron.nl/asterics/lib/exe/fetch.php?tok=d3d107&media=http%3A%2F%2Fandromeda.star.bris.ac.uk%2Ftopcat%2Ftutorial-asterics1%2F|here]]
   
15:30 -- 16:00 Coffee break

   * Multimessenger astrophysics and open science
   * Prospects for joint GW and high-energy EM observations of NS-NS mergers (Barbara) {{:open:wp4:dadi2016-barbara.pdf|pdf}}
   * LIGO Open Science Center (Roy - {{:open:wp4:losc.pdf|pdf}}) and Virgo plans (Eric) 
   * Follow-up strategies



17:30 Session closes

19:30 Workshop dinner

**Jun 1st** //Salle de réunion coupôle//

9:00 Welcome

   * Galaxy catalogs for GW follow-up
   * Gergely Dalya: “The current state of GLADE” {{open:wp4:gdalya_glade_eurovo.pdf|pdf}}
   * Gabor Galgocy: "Planned future development of GLADE” {{open:wp4:galgoczi_euvo.pdf|pdf}}

10:30 -- 11:00 Coffee break

   * Follow-up strategies
   * Tiling strategies of wide FOV optical telescopes (Shaon) {{open:wp4:presentation_ghosh.pdf|pdf}}
   * MassBus: virtual observatory for gravitational-wave follow-up (Roy) ({{:open:wp4:massbus.pdf|pdf}})
   * Multimessenger astrophysics and open science

 12:30 -- 14:00 Lunch break

   * VO tools for astronomers
   * The BlackGEM array -- needs of VO tools  (Steven) {{open:wp4:bloemen_20160531.pdf|pdf}}
   * Meeting summary. What's next?
   * Small group meetings/Hackathon   

16:00 Meeting ends
